# 🔑 AAA (Authentication, Authorization & Accounting)

AAA defines **who you are**, **what you're allowed to do**, and **what you did**.

## AAA Components

| Component | Definition | Question Answered | Example | Common Technologies |
|-----------|------------|-------------------|---------|---------------------|
| **Authentication** | Verifies the identity of a user or system. | Who are you? | Logging in using username, password, MFA, or biometrics. | Kerberos, LDAP, RADIUS, TACACS+, OAuth, SAML |
| **Authorization** | Determines what an authenticated user is allowed to access. | What are you allowed to do? | HR can view payroll, but interns cannot. | RBAC, ABAC, ACLs, IAM Policies |
| **Accounting (Auditing)** | Records and tracks user activities. | What did you do? | Logging login times, accessed files, and executed commands. | Syslog, SIEM, Windows Event Logs, Audit Logs |

---

## 💡 Easy Way to Remember

| AAA Component | Think Of |
|--------------|----------|
| **Authentication** | 👤 Who are you? |
| **Authorization** | 🔑 What can you do? |
| **Accounting** | 📝 What did you do? |

---

## Example

An employee logs into the company VPN.

### Authentication

- Username
- Password
- Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)

### Authorization

- ✅ Allowed to access the internal Git repository
- ❌ Denied access to the HR database

### Accounting

- Login time recorded
- IP address logged
- Files accessed logged
- Logout time recorded

