# 💾 Three States of Data

Data must be protected regardless of where it exists.

## Data States

| State | Definition | Example | Common Threats | Security Controls |
|------|------------|---------|----------------|-------------------|
| **Data at Rest** | Stored data that is not actively moving. | Hard drives, SSDs, databases, cloud storage, backups | Physical theft, ransomware, unauthorized access | Full Disk Encryption, Database Encryption, Access Controls, Backup Encryption |
| **Data in Transit** | Data moving between devices or networks. | HTTPS, SSH, VPN, Emails | Man-in-the-Middle (MitM), Packet Sniffing, Session Hijacking | TLS/SSL, VPN, IPSec, SSH, Certificate Validation |
| **Data in Use** | Data actively being processed in memory. | Running applications, RAM, CPU processing | Memory scraping, malware, code injection | Secure Enclaves, Endpoint Protection, Least Privilege, Memory Encryption |

---

## 💡 Easy Way to Remember

| Data State | Think Of |
|-----------|----------|
| **Data at Rest** | 📦 Sitting on a shelf |
| **Data in Transit** | 🚚 Travelling on the road |
| **Data in Use** | ⚙️ Being worked on |

---

## Example

Opening a PDF stored in OneDrive.

| Stage | Data State |
|--------|------------|
| Before opening | 📦 Data at Rest |
| Downloading the file | 🚚 Data in Transit |
| Reading it in Adobe Reader | ⚙️ Data in Use |

---

# 🔄 Relationship Between CIA, AAA & Data States

```text
Data States
│
├── Data at Rest
├── Data in Transit
└── Data in Use
          │
          ▼
      CIA Triad
 ┌──────┼──────┐
 ▼      ▼      ▼
Conf. Integrity Availability
          │
          ▼
          AAA
 ┌──────┼──────┐
 ▼      ▼      ▼
Auth.  Author. Accounting
```

## Summary

| Concept | Purpose | Focus |
|----------|---------|-------|
| 🔺 **CIA Triad** | Defines the security objectives. | What should be protected? |
| 🔑 **AAA** | Controls access and accountability. | Who can access what, and what actions were performed? |
| 💾 **Data States** | Identifies where data exists. | Where must security controls be applied? |

---

> **Remember**
>
> - **CIA** defines the **security goals**.
> - **AAA** enforces **access control and accountability**.
> - **Data States** describe **where data exists**, ensuring appropriate protections are applied throughout its lifecycle.